				p
					| Teresa is a manual spinal physical therapist with over 30 years of clinical experience. A graduate of the prestigious Columbia University school of Physical Therapy, Teresa has spent several years perfecting her clinical skills and expertise in a variety of settings. She has been in practice in the Houston medical center area since 1983, and in 1998 completed a long-standing mechanical spinal curriculum by passing her certification in mechanical diagnosis and treatment from 
					strong The McKenzie Institute
					| . In 1999, she was designated a Level 3 therapist, the highest level of clinical expertise in this region.
